article.description: Jarekious Bradley has 5 3s and 23 points for SE Missouri State in 102-72 win over Tulane
article.headline: Jarekious Bradley has 5 3s and 23 points for SE Missouri State in 102-72 win over Tulane
article.linkText: Jarekious Bradley has 5 3s and 23 points for SE Missouri State in 102-72 win over Tulane
article.story: PUERTO VALLARTA, Mexico -- Jarekious Bradley led Southeast Missouri State with 23 points in a 102-72 victory over Tulane on Saturday in the Cure UCD Classic in Puerto Vallarta. The Redhawks (5-2) broke tournament records they had just set the night before by making 16 3-pointers and shooting 59.3 percent from the field. They outrebounded the Green Wave 37-22 and took the lead for good on an 8-0 run that made the score 21-13 with 8:46 left in the first half. Nino Johnson had 10 points and 12 rebounds and Darrian Gray had 15 points and five assists. Antonius Cleveland had 17 points, Tyler Stone added 14 and Jamaal Calvin scored 13. Bradley was 5 of 9 from 3-point range. The Redhawks won both games this year after having gone 0-2 in the first Cure UCD Classic a year ago. Jonathan Stark led Tulane (4-4) with 21 points and Louis Dabney had 20.
